title: JJ the Rooster Memorial Road Race
description: The JJ the Rooster Memorial Circuit Race will take place just east of the Shelby Forest General Store. This will be a straight category based race. All Masters and Juniors racers will race within their category.
course:
The course is a 4.2 mile loop of all right turns. Pavement conditions vary, but the entire loop is paved. Final mile of this course is a gradual uphill.

Follow this link to view the race course: http://www.mapmyride.com/routes/view/176539806
registration:
Registration for the Category 5 race will begin at 7:00 am and will close at 8:00 am. If the Cat 5 race exceeds 50 racers, we will split the race based on age. 

Pro/1/2/3 race registration will start at 9:00 am and will close at 10:15 am. 

Race fees are $25 (plus processing fee) up until 4/2/2013, at which point the fee increases to $30 (plus processing fee). Day of race registration is 35 dollars, plus a 3% processing fee.
notes:
Pro/1/2/3 racers will complete 13 laps for a total of 54.6 miles.

Category 4 and Women 1/2/3/4 will complete 10 laps for a total of 42 miles.

Category 5 racers will complete 8 laps for a total of 33.6 miles.

For race information, please contact Bryant Funston via email at bryant@buildpeakcompete.com.
directions:
From Little Rock:
Head east on I-40 and follow signs to Nashville.
Take Exit 2A toward US-51/Millington
Merge onto TN-300 W
Exit right onto US-51/Thomas St and head North for 3 miles
Take left turn onto N. Watkins and travel roughly 7 miles to the race staging area.

From Nashville:
- Take exit 24 - 25 for Tennessee 385 W toward Millington
- Merge onto I-269 N/Paul W Barret Pkwy and go 16.5
- Continue onto TN-3 S/US-51 S - 4.3 mi
- Turn right onto Rust Ave for 0.2 mi
- Take the 2nd right onto Woodstock Cuba Rd for 2.1 mi
- Turn left onto Little John Rd for 0.8 mi
- Turn right onto Walsh Rd for .0.5 mi
- Take the 2nd left onto Walsh Cove for 0.6 mi
- Take the 1st right onto TN-388 N/N Watkins Rd and race venue will be roughly 1 mile on the right.

title: Aaron Shafer Memorial Road Bike Race
2013 USA Cycling Pro Road Race & TT Nationals
I AM Mountain: Hamilton Creek Race
description: A mountain bike race and family festival at the Hamilton Creek Mountain Bike Trail. Events include a fast Short Track race, an individual Time Trial, and a Cross Country race that includes both sides of the trail.
course: Hamilton Creek is considered the most technical trail in the Nashville area. Most of the trail features are natural rock formations that test a riders skill and endurance. A full lap is roughly 10.5 miles and 1000 feet of elevation - and you\'ll fight for every inch.
registration: Registration coming soon.  All riders must sign a USA Cycling waiver on-site.  Any Pro and Cat 1 riders must possess an annual license.  Any Cat 2 and Cat 3 riders may purchase the one day option to participate.  $50 registration fee grants racers access to all three race events, plus fun bike activities, and includes a ticket to the food, beverages and festivities at the post-race concert on the waterfront at Hamilton Creek Park. Additional festival tickets available via registration. Free festival attendance to all participants under 14.
directions:
From Nashville, take I-40 to Stewarts Ferry Pike. Follow Stewarts Ferry Pike to the Hamilton Creek Mountain Bike Park. 

Address: Hamilton Creek Park
Nashville, TN 37217
United States

Tour de Paris - Tennessee
description:
The most exciting RR's of West and Middle TN in Paris Landing!  Featuring terrain in both Henry and Stewart Counties, this race will be challenging, but provide exciting road races that have not been seen in the area.

This is a stage race, so you will need to start and finish each stage to be eligible for the overall prize money.  Additional upgrade points are available based on your overall finish.
course: The Saturday road race will be on a 45 mile loop.  The course map can be found at this link: https://maps.google.com/maps/ms?vps=2&hl=en&ie=UTF8&oe=UTF8&msa=0&msid=201233865808077483466.0004ce3ca3b270d6a58fc .  The Sunday road race will be an 86.3 mile race taking part of Saturdays course, and extending it across Kentucky Lake.  The course map for Sunday can be found at this link: https://maps.google.com/maps/ms?vps=1&hl=en&ie=UTF8&oe=UTF8&msa=0&msid=201233865808077483466.0004ceef31b68be3ff633.
registration: Pre-registration infromation can be found at www.procyclingmiami.com, or directly at BikeReg.  Packet pick-up will be on-site on Friday, August 9th at Paris Landing State Park, or on race day starting at 6:30 AM.  Registration fee is $75 for this race, and you must register, start and complete both events to be eligible for overall prize purse
notes:
Held under USA Cycling event permit.  USA Cycling rules apply.  There is no one-day licenses sold for this race due to the category restrictions to allow for higher field limits.  The race will feature a rolling enclosure, so the entire road will be available for racing.  Race officials, and police support will be on the road, so riders will need to follow official instructions at all times.  Helmets are to be worn at all times while on the bike.

RESERVATION: 18002508614
USE CODE FOR SPECIAL PRICE: RACE

title: Memphis Velo Gran Fondo Fun Ride
Hoover Ride for Hope-Presented By Ride615
Clarksville Cyclocross Challenge
description: Riverside Bicycle Shop presents the Clarksville Cyclocross Challenge at Rotary Park.
course: A fast, short course (1.1 mi) over mixed terrain. The course is mostly over grass, with short sections of gravel, pavement, groomed singletrack, and sand.
registration:
Online registration through USA Cycling. Add $5 to register on the day of the event. One-day licenses $10.
	Race day registration and packet pick up available on race day at 8:30 AM.
	You must register at least 15 minutes before any race you enter.
	$20.00 pre-register for all categories except Juniors and Novice. Add $5 if registering on day of event
	$10.00 for Juniors
	$15.00 for Novice category which includes the cost of a one-day USA Cycling license.
	Everyone except beginners can compete in a additional races for only $5 each race.
	All racers must present a valid racing license or authorization to ride form. Unlicensed riders will be required to purchase a one-day license or annual license and will be placed in the Mens CX5, Womens CX4, Single Speed, or Masters (35+, 45+) Categories.. All riders will be required to complete and sign a standard athlete entry release form
	One-day licenses available at registration for $10. Annual licenses available at registration for $60.
All start times are Central <> Total payouts will not exceed $499.00 per category per day <> Novice Class races are for racers NOT holding any other USA Cycling annual license, male and female 18+ years old. First time racers only please.
notes:
Race held under USAC Permit #2013-3383
	Race numbers will be issued when you register. Use the same number for all races entered that day.
	Race is sanctioned by USA Cycling and all USA Cycling rules apply
	Riders must wear a CPSC approved helmet
	Entry fees include $3.00 for USA Cycling insurance coverage and $2.00 for TBRA surcharge
	There will be no refunds
	Race will be held regardless of weather conditions
	Organizer reserves the right to combine fields. Fields with fewer than four riders may be combined or cancelled
	Protest period is 15 minutes after the results are posted
	Bar ends must be removed from mountain bikes
	All bicycles must have a freewheel and two working brakes
directions:
2308 Rotary Park Drive, Clarksville, TN 37043. Google correctly maps this address.
	There is very limited vehicle parking inside the park. Also, the entire park IS NOT closed for the event. To allow others to continue to enjoy the park, event parking is available at Wall Construction outside the gates of the park. Please park there and ride or walk to the event area. Follow signage to the registration area.
